    <abstract>
      <t>Bit Index Explicit Replication (BIER) is a new multicast forwarding paradigm which doesn't require an explicit tree-building protocol and doesn't require intermediate routers to maintain any multicast state. This document proposes a transport-independent BIER encapsulation header which is applicable in any kind of transport networks.</t>
